title: Carousel style font and dot font identification
author: antheasmyth

comments.content:
Similar to Douglas Day's Bracelet Victorian, scanned from Tschichold's "Treasury of Alphabets and Lettering" [http://www.fontspace.com/douglas-day/braceletvictorian](http://web.archive.org/web/20140901235214/http:/www.fontspace.com/douglas-day/braceletvictorian "http://www.fontspace.com/douglas-day/braceletvictorian")  
Don

"WORKERS..." must be **[Ewert](http://web.archive.org/web/20140901235214/http:/www.findmyfont.com/index.php/fonts/font-preview?fset=Google-Web-Fonts&ffam=Ewert%20-%20Regular&fid=06d3a4f67539bfe70ff5f8d9204d6d8f&fsize=60&text=WORKERS%20PLAYTIME&wrap=2)** by Johan Kallas [2011] part of Google Web Fonts

Good find Fivos. I will add to my demi-Tuscan index.  
Don
